gomodel:SYNGO_3113  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 30/4/2018 Pim\nFig.3: \"β1 and β3 integrins control GlyR lateral diffusion\"\nFig.4: \"1 and β3 integrins modulate GlyR confinement and dwell time at synapses\"\nFig.5: \"β1 and β3 integrins control gephyrin amount and exchanges at synapses\"\n\nLiteral: \"Altogether, our data indicate that the modulation of gephyrin synaptic turnover by β1 and β3 integrins controls the dwell time and the number of GlyRs at synapses.\". Experimental description: \"Primary cultures of spinal cord neurons were prepared from embryonic Sprague Dawley rats at day 14\", Online methods" ;
